<!-- CAVES -->
<section class="caves" id="caves">
  <div style="text-align:center">
    <div class="section-label">Architecture & Art</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Notable <span>Caves</span></h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="caves-grid">
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">01</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 1</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Mahayana Vihara · 5th Century CE</div>
      <p>Contains the famous Padmapani and Vajrapani Bodhisattva paintings — considered masterpieces of ancient Indian art, and among the finest murals ever created in the world.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">02</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 2</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Mahayana Vihara · 5th Century CE</div>
      <p>Remarkable for its ornate ceiling paintings featuring floral, geometric and figurative motifs. Shrines contain images of the Thousand Buddhas carved in intricate detail.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">10</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 10</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Hinayana Chaitya · 2nd Century BCE</div>
      <p>The oldest cave at Ajanta. A prayer hall featuring a large stupa at its apse, with traces of the earliest paintings — some of which bear inscriptions identifying donors.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">16</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 16</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Mahayana Vihara · 5th Century CE</div>
      <p>Features the poignant "Dying Princess" painting — depicting Nanda's wife Sundari fainting upon learning of her husband's intent to become a monk — a celebrated Jataka illustration.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">17</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 17</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Mahayana Vihara · 5th Century CE</div>
      <p>Known as the "cave of the finest paintings" — it contains the greatest variety and number of Jataka stories depicted through vivid, well-preserved murals across its walls and ceiling.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cave-card">
      <div class="cave-num">26</div>
      <div class="cave-name">Cave 26</div>
      <div class="cave-type">Mahayana Chaitya · 5th–6th Century CE</div>
      <p>Houses a magnificent 7-metre-long reclining Buddha in the Mahaparinirvana pose, surrounded by grieving disciples — one of the most dramatic sculptures in the entire complex.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

